<p>Time Traveling Parameters Control</p>

<p>In Part II the characters somehow get to a place where they can set the parameters for time travel:</p>
<p>- If the past can be changed or not.</p>
<p>- If paradoxes that something was never invented but rather the original idea came from an artifact that was brought from the future.</p>

<p>The PCs ask the supervisor if the control is stable, hence if you change one thing and change it back it will return to its original position. He answers that it isn't. Then they ask him if it has a save and restore mechanism. He answers that it does not.</p>

<p>-------------------</p>
<p>When the PCs get to Galku, and try to extract information out of him he sais: "What are you looking at me? I'm completely innocent. See no incredible selfishness and total in-consideration of everybody else's welfare and opinions. Hear no incredible selfishness and total in-consideration of everybody else's welfare and opinions."</p>

<p>-------------------</p>

<p>At a certain time, when the PCs explore the first castle, they get a chance to see their players. ("and now you will observe your true selves…"). While they are seeing them they are very awe-inspired and excited. Afterwards, they talk about all the things that changed in their players since the last time they saw them. At the end Bryte says "and did you see mine? Now she has a pony-tail."</p>

